quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,28,"And after him, We sent down no soldiers from heaven to his people, nor would We ever send any down."
  36,29,"<span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Abu Ja’far read it as: “Nothing happened but a single shout…”</span>
  36,30,"Alas for the servants! No messenger comes to them but they ridicule him."
  36,31,"Have they not seen how many generations We annihilated before them—that they will not return to them?"
  36,32,"And <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Ibn Amer, Asem, Hamza and Ibn Jammaz read it as: “And all of them, all together, will be arraigned before Us.”</span>
  36,33,"And there is a sign for them in the lifeless land: We have revived it and have brought out from it grains, so from it they eat."
  36,34,"And We have made in it gardens of palm-trees and grapevines, and have caused springs to burst forth in it,"
  36,35,"that they may eat from its produce and<i class=""s"">(from) </i>what{1}<span class=",footnotes:1:The word <i>ma</i><i> </i>in Arabic can mean ‘what’ or ‘not’; if interpreted as the latter, the meaning of the statement becomes “…that they may eat from its fruits, though their hands have not made it…”,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Shu’ba, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…from its produce and (from) their own handiwork…”</span>
  36,36,"Highly Exalted is He Who created all pairs—of what the earth germinates and of their own selves{1}and of what they do not know.",footnotes:1:i.e. Males and females.
  36,37,"And a sign for them is the night: We strip the day out of it—and they are suddenly in darkness."
  36,38,"And the sun runs towards its destination; such is the determining of the Almighty, the All-Knowing."
  36,39,"<span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Rouh read it as: “And the moon: We have determined it in phases…”</span>
  36,40,"The sun is not to overtake the moon, nor is the night to outpace the day, and each floats in an orbit."
